{:synth/id   :solar-filter
 :synth/tags [:filter :polivoks :12db :stereo :bus-aware :solar42]
 :synth/doc  "Dual cascaded 12dB/oct resonant LPF — Polivoks-style approximation.

  The Solar42 uses a pair of Polivoks-derived 12dB/oct lowpass filters. This synth
  approximates that topology by cascading two RLPF stages in series:

    In → RLPF(cutoff, res) → RLPF(cutoff, res) → Out

  Two 12dB stages in series produce 24dB/oct slope — a steeper, more aggressive
  character that honours the Polivoks heritage (though the analog character differs).

  Reads stereo from :in-bus (2 channels) and writes stereo to :out-bus.
  :cutoff is in the same [0–127] scale used across cljseq filters (× 125 Hz internally).
  :res is reciprocal Q (0–1; higher = more resonant, approaching self-oscillation)."
 :args  {:in-bus  8
         :out-bus 10
         :cutoff  60
         :res     0.35
         :amp     0.85}
 :graph [:out :out-bus
          [:* :amp
           [:rlpf
            [:rlpf [:in :in-bus 2] [:* :cutoff 125.0] :res]
            [:* :cutoff 125.0]
            :res]]]}
